rComments: He was one of the best instructors I've had in math at U of T. He knows his stuff and is very good at explaining abstract concepts in a way that is easy to understand. His tests and exams are difficult so make sure attend the lectures and do the recommended problems. And take advantage of his office hours!

He expects a lot of his students, but everyone in the Math department does.  I think some students here were just pissed that he wouldn't post class averages - but he explained that he was doing that so that we would do better (there's a study somewhere..?).  Anyway, he's pretty funny and genuinely seems to care about his students.
Teaches well, however he likes to throw too many hard questions and his final was extremely hard with an average 50%. Worst prof I ever has, his only sole purpose is to ruin gpas. Avoid at all costs

He may seem like a nice guy but don't let you throw you off, refuses to post solutions to hmwk problems, gives hard quizzes and his final was brutal,  if you have it, i recommend waiting for a different person to teach this course, avoid him at all costs!

He gives difficult quizzes and the examples in lecture are not sufficient to do well, a good lecture overall, Also, he refuses to post big list solutions which is very bad since you never know if your answer is correct
